The paper discusses the design of energy-efficient neuromorphic circuits, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The use of NEMS switches also involves the study of electromechanical systems (cs.ET) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). The paper also discusses the impact of NEM switches on leakage power, which is related to the field of architecture (cs.AR) and circuit design (cs.CE).
